# Icons: Use Lucide React

เมื่อต้องใช้ Icon ให้ใช้ **lucide-react** (Lucide Icons) เสมอ

When you need to add or suggest **icons** in the project, always use **Lucide React** (`lucide-react`).

## Do

- Import icons from `lucide-react`: `import { IconName } from 'lucide-react'`
- Prefer named imports for the icons you need (e.g. `ChevronDown`, `Settings`, `Search`)
- Use the same icon set as shadcn/ui (this project is configured with Lucide)

## Don't

- Don't add or suggest other icon libraries (e.g. react-icons, Heroicons, Font Awesome) for new UI
- Don't use emoji or Unicode symbols as a substitute when a Lucide icon exists

## Example

```tsx
import { ChevronDown, Settings } from 'lucide-react';

<Button variant="ghost" size="icon">
  <Settings className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>
```

## Reference

- Package: `lucide-react` (already in the project)
- Browse icons: https://lucide.dev/icons/
